   <notes>
The first public version 0.0.1 has the following features:
- Channel support
- Installing and uninstalling packages
- Switching options for installation: nodeps, alldeps, reqdeps
- Package list caching
- Working offline

You might note that the package transfer is very slow when starting
up the first time. This is because data for over 300 PEAR packages
need to be transferred, and for each package two separate HTTP
connections are made - currently there is no better way, but I&apos;m
in contact with Greg to get a better solution.
   </notes>
